# üìò Data Dictionary ‚Äî Allopathy Drugs in India

This data dictionary explains all fields used in the **Allopathy Drugs in India ‚Äì SQL + Power BI Project**,  
including both the **raw dataset columns** and the **derived analytical fields** created through SQL views.

---

## üßæ Base Dataset (Raw Data)
| Column Name | Data Type | Description | Example |
|--------------|------------|-------------|----------|
| **id** | INT | Unique identifier for each drug/product record. | 101245 |
| **name** | VARCHAR | Official or marketed name of the drug/product. | Paracetamol 500mg Tablet |
| **price** | DECIMAL(10,2) | Price per unit/pack as listed in the dataset. May contain zero or null values. | 32.50 |
| **is_discontinued** | BIT / INT | Product status flag ‚Äî 0 = Active, 1 = Discontinued. | 0 |
| **manufacturer_name** | VARCHAR | Name of the company/manufacturer producing the drug. | Cipla Ltd |
| **type** | VARCHAR | Drug type ‚Äî Allopathy, Ayurvedic, or Homeopathic. | Allopathy |
| **pack_size_label** | VARCHAR | Packaging size or label (e.g., 10 Tablets, 100 ml Bottle). | 10 Tablets |
| **short_composition1** | VARCHAR | Primary active composition/ingredient. | Paracetamol |
| **short_composition2** | VARCHAR | Secondary or additional composition/ingredient (if any). | Caffeine |

---

## üßÆ Derived Columns (SQL Transformations in `base` View)
| Column Name | Data Type | Description | Example |
|--------------|------------|-------------|----------|
| **price** | DECIMAL(18,2) | Cleaned and converted numeric price from raw data using `TRY_CONVERT`. | 25.00 |
| **sc1** | VARCHAR | Trimmed and cleaned value of `short_composition1`. | Paracetamol |
| **sc2** | VARCHAR | Trimmed and cleaned value of `short_composition2`. | Caffeine |

---

## üîó `composition_pairs` View
| Column Name | Data Type | Description | Example |
|--------------|------------|-------------|----------|
| **id** | INT | Drug/product ID linked to base dataset. | 101245 |
| **manufacturer_name** | VARCHAR | Manufacturer associated with the drug. | Cipla Ltd |
| **composition_pair** | VARCHAR | Combined pair of active ingredients, ordered alphabetically for consistency. | Caffeine, Paracetamol |

---

## ‚öñÔ∏è `active_vs_inactive` View
| Column Name | Data Type | Description | Example |
|--------------|------------|-------------|----------|
| **manufacturer_name** | VARCHAR | Manufacturer name. | Sun Pharma |
| **total_products** | INT | Total number of products by the manufacturer. | 210 |
| **active_count** | INT | Count of active (non-discontinued) products. | 180 |
| **discontinued_count** | INT | Count of discontinued products. | 30 |
| **active_rate** | DECIMAL(5,2) | Percentage of active products. | 85.71 |
| **discontinued_rate** | DECIMAL(5,2) | Percentage of discontinued products. | 14.29 |

---

## üß™ `all_compositions` View
| Column Name | Data Type | Description | Example |
|--------------|------------|-------------|----------|
| **composition** | VARCHAR | Flattened list of all compositions (from both `short_composition1` and `short_composition2`). | Amoxicillin |

---

## üè≠ Manufacturer Analysis Table (Aggregated)
| Column Name | Data Type | Description | Example |
|--------------|------------|-------------|----------|
| **manufacturer_name** | VARCHAR | Company or manufacturer name. | Torrent Pharmaceuticals |
| **avg_price** | DECIMAL(10,2) | Average product price per manufacturer. | 48.75 |
| **min_price** | DECIMAL(10,2) | Minimum product price for that manufacturer. | 3.50 |
| **max_price** | DECIMAL(10,2) | Maximum product price for that manufacturer. | 265.00 |
| **item_count** | INT | Total number of products listed. | 154 |
| **manufacturer_diversity** | INT | Count of distinct composition pairs offered. | 27 |

---

## üì¶ Pack Size Analysis
| Column Name | Data Type | Description | Example |
|--------------|------------|-------------|----------|
| **pack_size_label** | VARCHAR | Label representing packaging unit or dosage count. | 10 Tablets |
| **average_price** | DECIMAL(10,2) | Average price of drugs under the given pack size. | 55.60 |
| **items_count** | INT | Total number of products for the given pack size. | 1425 |

---

## üß∞ Summary of Relationships
| Relationship | Description |
|---------------|-------------|
| **base ‚Üí composition_pairs** | One-to-one (based on drug `id`) |
| **base ‚Üí active_vs_inactive** | One-to-many (grouped by `manufacturer_name`) |
| **composition_pairs ‚Üí manufacturer_diversity** | Aggregated by `manufacturer_name` |
| **base ‚Üí pack_size_label** | One-to-many for pack size analysis |

---

## üóÇÔ∏è Data Coverage
| Category | Count / Range |
|-----------|----------------|
| Total Products | 253,793 |
| Unique Manufacturers | ~5,000+ |
| Distinct Compositions | ~7,000+ |
| Price Range | ‚Çπ0.50 ‚Äì ‚Çπ20,000+ |
| Pack Sizes | 10 Tablets, 100 ml Bottle, 1 Strip, etc. |
| Active vs Discontinued Ratio | ~85% Active : 15% Discontinued |

---

## üìÑ Notes
- Null and zero prices were excluded from analytical calculations.  
- Composition combinations are alphabetically ordered to prevent duplicates.  
- Manufacturer diversity represents the **breadth of unique formulation pairs** per company.  
- Pack size trends were evaluated only for records with valid price data.

---

‚úÖ **Total Columns (Raw + Derived):** 20+  
‚úÖ **Total Views Created:** `base`, `composition_pairs`, `active_vs_inactive`, `all_compositions`  
‚úÖ **Database Engine:** Microsoft SQL Server  
‚úÖ **Visualization Layer:** Power BI  

